text: ALASKA:  There were 7.0 days suitable for fieldwork last week.  Temperatures last week ranged from two degrees below normal
label: BODY

text: near Fairbanks to nine degrees above normal on Kodiak.  Precipitation varied with most of the major growing areas receiving some
label: BODY

text: rain.     Rate of crop growth was reported as 15% moderate, 85% rapid.
label: BODY

text: TANANA VALLEY:  An average of 7.0 days was suitable for fieldwork.  Rate of crop growth was reported as 100% rapid.  Farm
label: BODY

text: activities for the week included planting forage oats, scouting and spraying weeds, irrigation systems are up and running, fence
label: BODY

text: construction and general farm maintenance. High tunnels, greenhouses and truck farms are planted.  Farmers markets are open and
label: BODY

text: selling early season vegetables and bedding plants.  IPM techs are visiting farms for livestock and filed pests.
label: BODY

text: MATANUSKA VALLEY:  An average of 6.5 days was suitable for fieldwork.  Rate of crop growth was reported as 25% moderate,
label: BODY

text: 75% rapid.  Farm activities for the week included planting vegetables, irrigation, weed control, harvesting hay, fertilizing for second
label: BODY

text: cutting, general farm maintenance. Farmers markets are selling vegetables, honey and bedding/nursery plants.
label: BODY

text: KENAI PENINSULA:    An average of 7.0 days was suitable for fieldwork.  Rate of crop growth was reported as 40% moderate,
label: BODY

text: 60% rapid.  Farm activities for the week included harvesting hay and preparing for the cutting season.
